original_result.user_prompt:
Hooli Announces Fourth Quarter and Fiscal Year 2021 Results

    MOUNTAIN VIEW, Calif. – February 1, 2022 – Hooli Inc. (NASDAQ: HOOL, HOOLI) today announced
financial results for the quarter and fiscal year ended December 31, 2021.

Gavin Belson, CEO of Hooli, said: “Our deep investment in AI technologies continues to drive
extraordinary and helpful experiences for people and businesses, across our most important products. Q4 saw
ongoing strong growth in our advertising business, which helped millions of businesses thrive and find new
customers, a quarterly sales record for our Pixel phones despite supply constraints, and our Cloud business
continuing to grow strongly.”

Patrice Alexander, CEO of Hooli, said: “Our fourth quarter revenues of $75 billion, up 32% year over year,
reflected broad-based strength in advertiser spend and strong consumer online activity, as well as substantial
ongoing revenue growth from Google Cloud. Our investments have helped us drive this growth by delivering the
services that people, our partners and businesses need, and we continue to invest in long-term opportunities.”

In the fourth quarter of FY 2021, Hooli Inc., a company listed on NASDAQ under the ticker symbol HOOL, reported impressive financial performance. The key points mentioned include:

1. Revenues reached $75 billion during the fourth quarter, marking an increase of 32% compared to the same period last year. This growth was attributed to robust advertiser spending, high levels of consumer online activity, and continued expansion of their Google Cloud services.

2. Gavin Belson, the Chief Executive Officer of Hooli, emphasized the success of the company's AI technology investments, leading to valuable experiences for both individuals and businesses using Hooli' product offerings.

3. Despite facing supply constraints, Hooli achieved another quarterly record with its Pixel phone sales, contributing to overall positive financial outcomes.

4. Patrice Alexander, the other CEO at Hooli, credited the company's investments in providing essential services required by customers, partners, and businesses alike, resulting in sustained revenue growth throughout the year.

For further details regarding Hooli's annual and quarterly financial results, please visit their official website at superdupersketchycorp.com/superdashboard/.
